The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Dec. 3: The Federation of Indian Commodity Exchange (FICE) is roping in the regional exchanges to join its initiative for a technology partnership with Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE). The technology tie-up is likely to be finalised during January-March 2006, FICE vice-president P.M. Chheda said here today. ?The federation has signed up agreement with six to seven exchanges of western India and will sign up Calcutta Jute Exchange next by mid-December followed by exchanges in the north India,? Chedda said.

 Mumbai, Dec. 3: Apollo Tyres Ltd has approved the sale, lease or disposal of its tube division. The company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange that the shareholders approved the disposal of the division through a postal ballot.

 Mumbai, Dec. 3: The Khemka group-promoted NEPC India Ltd has approved the sale and disposal of the assets and liabilities of its wind energy division. Its share-holders have approved the proposal, the company informed the stock exchanges.




